results.name: Air Max 90 'City Special - Chicago'
results.story: Dropping as part of the ‘City Special’ collection, the Nike Air Max 90 ‘Chicago’ pays homage to the Windy City. The retro runner showcases varying shades of crimson throughout the upper, midsole and outsole. ‘CHI’ branding appears on the custom sockliner and a small woven tag on the sneaker’s lateral side. Those details are joined by standard Air Max 90 features, including a cropped leather Swoosh, a Nike Air heel patch and a visible Max Air unit nestled in the heel of the polyurethane midsole.

results.name: Air Max 95 'City Special - NYC'
results.story: Releasing as part of the brand’s ‘City Special’ collection, the Nike Air Max 95 ‘NYC’ showcases a monochromatic yellow hue that pays tribute to New York’s taxicabs. A uniform finish is applied to the sneaker’s layered leather side panels, accented with a contrasting black NYC tag on the lateral heel. The retro runner is mounted on a yellow polyurethane midsole, enhanced with visible Max Air units in the heel and forefoot. Underfoot, a black rubber outsole features Nike’s iconic waffle traction pattern.

results.name: Nike Air VaporMax Plus City Special Atlanta
results.story: Launching as part of the ‘City Special’ series, the Nike Air VaporMax Plus ‘Atlanta’ pays tribute to the capital city of Georgia. A gradient blend of black and Mystic Green is executed on the textile upper, overlaid with a series of TPU ‘fingers’ and accented with a metallic gold Swoosh. Matching gold ATL lettering is inscribed on a woven tag attached to the lateral collar. The Air Max Plus upper is mounted on a foam midsole, complete with a whale tail-inspired midfoot shank, which sits atop a transparent VaporMax unit.

results.name: Wmns Waffle Racer Crater 'Pale Ivory Electric Green'
results.story: The Nike women’s Waffle Racer Crater ‘Pale Ivory Electric Green’ reinvents the vintage 1977 runner with refreshed details and a sustainable build. Semi-concealed laces secure recycled textile twill upper, finished in a subtle ivory hue and reinforced with grey suede overlays at the toe and heel. Neon green zigzag stitching surrounds the black leather Swoosh, matching the Nike branded leather heel tab. The sneaker rides on a Crater Foam midsole, supported by a classic waffle tread outsole made in part with Nike Grind.

results.name: Daybreak Type M2Z2 'Team Orange'
results.story: The Nike Daybreak Type M2Z2 ‘Team Orange’ delivers a sustainable take on the retro-inspired silhouette, featuring at least 20% recycled materials by weight. A stitched Swoosh adorns the grey textile upper, fortified with contrasting orange and green synthetic overlays. Distinctive speckling on the heel clip and waffle-tread rubber outsole indicates the use of Nike Grind, composed of recycled materials originating from manufacturing scraps and worn-out sneakers.

results.name: Nike Air Force 1 Low Rose White
results.story: The Nike Air Force 1 '07 LX ‘Thank You Plastic Bag’ celebrates the special bond between the AF1 and NYC, showcasing a design that pays homage to the city’s ubiquitous bodegas. The low-top’s leather upper is rendered in a monochromatic white finish, interrupted by red Nike branding on the tongue tag that replicates the repeating ‘Thank You’ graphic typically featured on a bodega’s plastic bags. The midsole is embellished with a red rose, its green stem integrated into the signature Nike Air branding.

results.name: Nike Dunk High Retro White Vast Grey (2021)
results.story: The Nike Dunk High ‘Vast Grey’ delivers an understated two-tone colorway of the vintage ‘80s hoops shoe originally developed for the college hardwood. The classic color blocking on the leather upper is reminiscent of the ‘Be True to Your School’ series, featuring a clean white base with subtle grey overlays and a matching grey Swoosh. The same neutral tones are repeated on the sneaker’s tooling, highlighted by a low-profile midsole and rubber outsole designed for pivoting.

results.name: Phantom GT Club DF MG GS 'Photo Blue'
Nike Air Force 1 Low Rose Pink
results.story: The Nike Air Force 1 ‘07 LX ‘Thank You Plastic Bag’ celebrates the enduring bond that connects NYC and the AF1, featuring a monochromatic Pink Foam leather upper that nods to the plastic bags used by the city’s numerous bodegas. Those disposable totes are referenced with a repeating Nike wordmark on the coated tongue tag, a red rose graphic on the white rubber midsole, and a Swooshed smiley face on the custom sockliner, underscored with the phrase ‘Have a Nike Day.’

results.name: Wmns React Infinity Run Flyknit 2 'Sunset Pulse'
Nike Dunk High Sail Football Grey (W)
results.story: The Nike women’s Dunk High ‘Football Grey’ delivers an understated colorway of the retro hoops shoe originally released in 1985, featuring an outsole borrowed from the Air Jordan 1 and an upper design redolent of both the Air Jordan 1 and Nike Terminator. Here, the leather upper makes use of an off-white base with contrasting overlays in a subtle pale blue finish. A padded mesh collar combines with a nylon tongue to deliver a comfortable fit.

results.name: Zoom Freak 2 'Taxi'
results.story: The Nike Zoom Freak 2 ‘Taxi’ takes inspiration from an incident during Giannis Antetokounmpo’s rookie year in Milwaukee: running late to practice and unsure of how to hail a taxi in his new hometown, the seven-footer resorted to legging it on the pavement before a helpful fan pulled over and offered a lift. The low-top makes use of a black textile upper with contrasting yellow and metallic silver accents. A taxicab-inspired checkerboard print decorates the heel tab, inscribed with ‘Off Duty’ on the left shoe and ‘34’ on the right.

results.name: Wmns Zoom Air Fire 'White Dark Beetroot'
results.story: The Nike women’s Zoom Air Fire 'White Dark Beetroot' combines plush cushioning with design cues borrowed from classic runners of the past. The upper is constructed from breathable white mesh with tonal synthetic overlays throughout. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a stacked foam midsole, housing a visible Zoom Air unit in the heel surrounded by a burgundy-colored TPU frame — a unique detail that recalls the tooling of the Air Zoom Spiridon Cage 2.

results.name: Nike Air Vapormax EVO NRG Air Max Day Mashup (2021)
results.story: The Nike Air VaporMax EVO NRG ‘Collector's Closet’ packs a compendium of Air Max history in a single pair of shoes. In addition to details lifted from seven different Air Max models, the sneaker features unique prints, colors and textures on each of the mismatched uppers. The left shoe pays homage to the ‘Warhawk’ and ‘Moon Landing’ Air Max 90, OG ‘Royal’ Air Max 1 and the CDG Air Max 180. The right gives the nod to the ‘Snakeskin’ Air Max 98, ‘Wotherspoon’ Air Max 1/97 and OG ‘Hyper Blue’ Air Max Plus. Those disparate elements are joined by reflective accents at the forefoot and heel.

results.name: Challenger OG 'Mean Green'
results.story: The Nike Challenger OG ‘Mean Green’ showcases a verdant finish on a near 1-to-1 remake of the heritage runner originally released in 1979. Recycled materials are incorporated into the green canvas upper, accented with a black Swoosh and contrasting grey paneling on the sneaker’s medial side. A recycled Volt-colored sockliner works in tandem with a springy foam midsole to deliver a cushioned ride. Underfoot, the speckled waffle-traction outsole is made with Nike Grind.

results.name: Air Max 270 Extreme TD 'Pure Platinum Blue Void'
LeBron 18 Low 'Neon Nights'
results.story: The Nike LeBron 18 Low ‘Neon Nights’ replaces the KnitPosite 2.0 build of its mid-top counterpart with breathable textile in a rich magenta finish. Contrasting black overlays at the toe and heel are good for lightweight support, while blue semi-translucent taping wraps under the forefoot for added containment. The low-top is mounted on a clear midsole, featuring a large-volume Max Air unit that extends from heel to arch. A matching translucent rubber outsole delivers grippy traction on the hardwood.

results.name: Force Zoom Trout 7 TF 'White Light Smoke Grey'
Nike PG 5 Play for the Future
Air Max Excee AMD GS 'White Indigo Burst'
Air Force 1 Low CR7 By You
Nike Air Max 90 Light Violet Champagne (W)
Nike SB Dunk Low VX1000
results.story: The Nike Dunk Low SB ‘Camcorder’ takes inspiration from an iconic piece of equipment that was instrumental in the proliferation of skate videos in the ‘90s: the Sony DCR VX1000 camcorder. The low-top makes use of a charcoal nubuck upper, accented with a lighter shade of grey on the forefoot overlay and signature Swoosh. The black synthetic leather heel overlay is embellished with a series of camcorder functions, including ‘SHUTTER SPEED’ and ‘REC LEVEL.’ Red and yellow eyelets, along with a mint green heel tab, add subtle pops of color to the neutral color scheme.

results.name: Air Max 90 Leather GS 'Black Sunset Pulse'
ZoomX Vaporfly NEXT% 'Blue Ribbon Sports'
results.story: The Nike ZoomX Vaporfly NEXT% 'Blue Ribbon Sports' updates the marathon runner with a graphic print inspired by Nike’s precursor brand. The all-over design enlivens the lightweight VaporWeave upper, featuring off-center lacing and a wider toe box for a roomier fit. Responsive cushioning arrives via a stacked Zoom X foam midsole, its energy returning properties enhanced by a full-length carbon fiber plate. Vertical flex grooves are built into the outsole, reinforced with durable rubber in high-wear areas.

results.name: Nike Challenger OG Dark Smoke Grey
Air Force 1/1 Unlocked By You
results.story: Offered through the brand’s customization platform, the Nike Air Force 1/1 Unlocked By You provides an especially wide range of personalized options. The midfoot and heel panels — available in leather, suede and ripstop — can be swapped out, as the sneaker features a hook-and-loop base. Additionally, wearers can choose between a standard or jewel Swoosh. Tooling is consistent with the standard Air Force 1 build, equipped with encapsulated Nike Air cushioning in the heel.

results.name: Kyrie 7 'Midnight Navy'
results.story: The Nike Kyrie 7 ‘Midnight Navy’ enlivens the performance hoops shoe with vivid colors and dynamic graphics. The sneaker’s open mesh construction reveals contrasting red and blue tones on the textile underlay, while the heel panel features a modified version of Kyrie Irving’s all-seeing eye graphic, surrounded by bold lines radiating outward. A Phylon midsole, housing a forefoot Air Zoom Turbo unit, is undergirded by a fluorescent green rubber outsole.

results.name: Nike Dunk Low Retro Medium Grey Varsity Red UNLV (2021)
results.story: The 2021 reissue of the Nike Dunk Low SP ‘UNLV’ revives one of the original colorways of the 1985 ‘Be True to Your School’ series, albeit in low-top form. The sneaker is rendered in the signature colors of the University of Las Vegas, highlighted by a neutral grey leather base with contrasting University Red overlays. A padded collar and breathable nylon tongue combine for a comfortable fit, the latter accented with a woven Nike tag in the same grey and red color scheme.

results.name: Stussy x Air Huarache LE TD 'Dark Olive' 2021
Stussy x Air Huarache LE TD 'Desert Oak' 2021
results.story: This 2021 reissue of the Stussy x Nike Air Huarache LE TD ‘Desert Oak’ revives a historic 2000 collaboration for new generation of retro sneaker enthusiasts. Like the original, this pair dresses the Swooshless runner in subdued earth tones, highlighted by an off-white textile build with light brown nubuck overlays. A molded heel cage in olive green adds structural support to the bootie-style upper, while a soft foam midsole offers lightweight cushioning with each step.

results.name: Wmns Metcon 6 'Vast Grey Dark Atomic Teal'
results.colorway: Vast Grey/Astronomy Blue/Dark Atomic Teal/Pink Glow

results.name: Nike Dunk Low Coast (W)
results.story: The Nike women’s Dunk Low ‘Coast’ highlights traditional two-tone color blocking on a leather upper that maintains the look of the original 1985 release. A crisp white base, replete with perforated detailing on the toe box, is contrasted by overlays in a vibrant blue finish. Nike branding on the heel tab and woven tongue tag are rendered in an unexpected pop of yellow. The sneaker rides on a low-profile midsole, supported by a rubber outsole featuring concentric circle tread.

results.name: Nike Dunk Low Retro Hyper Cobalt (2021)
results.story: The Nike Dunk Low ‘Hyper Cobalt’ could be mistaken for an original 1985 colorway, featuring OG-style two-tone color blocking and a crisp white midsole. The leather upper combines a black base with contrasting blue overlays and a matching signature Swoosh. Traditional branding hits take the form of a woven Nike tongue tag, an embroidered Nike wordmark on the heel tab, and a Nike logo stamped on the sockliner in an unexpected pop of orange coloring.

results.name: Nike Air Total Max Uptempo Bred
results.story: The Nike Air Total Max Uptempo ‘Bred’ brings back a vintage hoops shoe originally released in 1997. The materials and color blocking mirror the OG Black/Volt colorway, with the older shoe’s neon accents replaced by University Red. The upper combines black tumbled leather with tonal nubuck overlays, patent leather trim, mesh construction around the collar and a mirror-reflective insert embedded in the heel. The mid-top rides on a Phylon midsole, enhanced with a red-tinged full-length Max Air unit.

results.name: Air Max 270 Extreme PS 'Pure Platinum Blue Void'
NikeCourt Air Zoom GP Turbo 'Obsidian Metallic Gold'
Nike Air Force 1 Shadow White Electric Green (W)
Nike Air Max 95 NDSTRKT Black Reflective
Flex Runner PS 'Dark Smoke Grey Game Royal'
Nike Go FlyEase Celestine Blue
results.story: The Nike Go FlyEase ‘Volt Celestine Blue’ showcases pastel hues on a revolutionary sneaker that introduces hands-free functionality as part of the brand’s easy-entry FlyEase initiative. The sneaker’s defining feature is the bi-stable hinge, which works in tandem with a midsole tensioner to keep the shoe secure in its fully open and closed states. When open, the insole is raised at an angle that allows the foot to intuitively slide in while pressing down, collapsing the midsole and locking it in place.

results.name: Wmns Flex Experience Run 10 'White Metallic Gold Star'
Wmns React Infinity Run Flyknit 2 'Particle Grey'
Swarovski x Air Max 97 Golf NRG 'Black Oracle Pink'
Nike Go FlyEase Dynamic Turquoise
results.story: The Nike GO FlyEase ‘Dynamic Turquoise’ delivers a stealthy debut colorway of the groundbreaking laceless sneaker that enables hands-free on and off. When open, a bi-stable hinge props up the back of the insole at an angle that allows the foot to intuitively slide in and press down, collapsing the two-piece midsole and locking it in place. A rubber midsole tensioner extends from the toe and around the back of the heel, working in concert with the paten-pending hinge to keep the sneaker secure in both its open and closed states.

results.name: Nike Go FlyEase Black
results.story: The Nike Go FlyEase ‘Black’ represents one of three introductory colorways of the brand’s revolutionary hands-free sneaker. The unique technology that underpins the shoe’s accessibility is the patent-pending bi-stable hinge, secured with a rubber midsole tensioner that extends from the toe and wraps around the back of the heel. When the hinge is open, the back of the insole is raised in the air at a roughly 30-degree angle, allowing the foot to easily slip on and collapse the hinge. To take off the shoe, the wearer steps on the ‘kickstand’ heel and simply steps out.

results.name: Flex Runner GS 'Smoke Grey Pink Foam'
Nike Air Griffey Max 1 White Freshwater (2021)
results.story: The 2021 reissue of the Nike Air Griffey Max 1 ‘Freshwater’ brings back the OG colorway of Ken Griffey Jr.’s debut signature shoe in celebration of its 25th anniversary. An adjustable ankle strap — embellished with raised Nike branding and Junior’s 24 jersey number with the Seattle Mariners — secures an upper built with white synthetic leather and black nubuck. Teal accents land on the sneaker’s webbing pull tabs and visible Max Air units, which enhance the heel and forefoot of the bulky polyurethane midsole.

results.name: Nike NDSTRKT Air Max 95 Neon
results.story: As suggested by its moniker, the Nike Air Max 95 NDSTRKT ‘Neon’ updates the lifestyle runner with an extra-durable build. Reflective neon webbing straps are integrated into the laces, securing a mesh upper reinforced with rubberized overlays and a molded TPU cage that extends across the midfoot. While the midsole maintains the look of the original Air Max 95, highlighted by visible Nike Air cushioning in the heel and forefoot, the outsole features a modified traction pattern designed to handle the elements.

results.name: Nike Air Max 2 CB 94 White Varsity Purple (2021)
Phantom Scorpion Academy DF MG GS 'Secret Tournament Pack'
Air Force 1 Low 'Topography Pack - White University Red'
Nike Air Force 1 07 QS Valentine's Day Love Letter
Nike Air Huarache Stussy Desert Oak (2021) (PS)
results.story: Crafted for little kids, the 2021 edition of the Stussy x Nike Air Huarache LE PS ‘Desert Oak’ brings back a groundbreaking collaboration that originally released in 2000 exclusively at Stussy’s London chapter store. The vintage silhouette features a shiny off-white textile upper, fortified with light brown nubuck overlays and an olive green TPU heel cage. A red Huarache tongue patch provides a contrasting pop of color. The Swooshless design is supported by a soft foam midsole with encapsulated Nike Air cushioning.

results.name: Nike Air Huarache Stussy Dark Olive (2021) (PS)
Nike Air Huarache Stussy Desert Oak (2021)
results.story: The 2021 release of the Stussy x Nike Air Huarache LE ‘Desert Oak’ brings back a groundbreaking release from 2000, developed as a collaboration between Nike’s Fraser Cooke and Stussy UK’s Michael Koppleman and launched exclusively at Stussy’s London chapter store. This reissue is true to the original, featuring a shiny cream-colored textile upper with light brown nubuck overlays and an olive green heel cage. A contrasting pop of red lands on the rubber Huarache tongue patch.  May run small, we suggest going up half a size.

results.name: Nike Air Force 1 Low Pixel SE White Leopoard (W)
Nike Air Huarache Stussy Dark Olive (2021)
results.story: The 2021 edition of the Stussy x Nike Air Huarache LE ‘Dark Olive’ revives a 2000 collaboration developed by Nike’s Fraser Cooke and Stussy UK’s Michael Koppleman, released exclusively through Stussy’s London chapter store. Tinker Hatfield’s retro runner makes use of a white and yellow textile upper with contrasting nubuck overlays at the toe and midfoot. In lieu of a traditional heel counter, the sneaker utilizes a Nike branded strap that wraps around the heel. A rubber Huarache patch in green and yellow decorates the tongue.  May run small, we suggest going up half a size.

results.name: Nike Air Force 1 Low Silver Snake (2021)
results.story: The 2021 reissue of the Nike Air Force 1 ‘3M Snake’ brings back one of three CO.JP Air Force 1 ‘B’ styles that originally released in 2001. The low-top features a black leather upper with reflective matte silver overlays and a faux snakeskin Swoosh. Tonal Nike branding is embroidered on the the black leather heel tab, while a classic woven tongue tag adorns the black leather tongue. The sneaker sits atop an Air-infused midsole, supported underfoot by a pivot-point rubber outsole.

results.name: Mercurial Superfly 8 Academy MG GS 'Black Cyber'
Nike ACG Mountain Fly Low Black Anthracite
Nike ACG Air Nasu Gore-Tex Clay Green
results.story: Named after Mount Nasu in Japan, the Nike ACG Air Nasu GTX ‘Clay Green’ features a rugged build developed for outdoor adventures. Toggle laces secure the black textile upper, lined in waterproof Gore-Tex and accented with fused olive green overlays that nod to classic ACG models from the ‘90s, including the Air Wallowa, Air Humara and Air Terra Grand. Reflective detailing on the webbing eyelets and heel tab offers added visibility in low-light conditions. Underfoot, a lugged rubber outsole delivers grippy traction on off-road terrain.

results.name: Air Max Axis GS 'Light Smoke Grey Sunset Pulse'
results.colorway: Light Smoke Grey/Dark Smoke Grey/Sapphire/Sunset Pulse

results.name: Nike DBreak Type Wolf Grey
results.story: The Nike DBreak-Type ‘Wolf Grey’ presents a contemporary interpretation of the original Daybreak running shoe. The lightweight build features an airy mesh upper in a pastel blue finish, reinforced by grey suede overlays and a rigid heel piece. Decorative stitched detailing and an exposed-foam tongue add to the deconstructed look. The sneaker rides on a soft foam midsole, supported underfoot by Nike’s iconic waffle outsole.

results.name: Mercurial Vapor 14 Academy FG MG 'Black Cyber'
